  keywords="is sh a scrabble word, sh scrabble, sh valid scrabble, sh sowpods only, vowelless scrabble words, sh meaning scrabble, words without vowels scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Is SH a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)",
    "description": "SH is valid in SOWPODS but NOT in TWL. It scores 5 points and is an interjection meaning 'quiet'.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-23",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-sh-a-scrabble-word" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is SH a valid Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SH is valid ONLY in SOWPODS (International/Collins dictionary). It is NOT valid in TWL (Tournament Word List used in North America). SH scores 5 points (S=1, H=4) and is an interjection meaning 'be quiet' or 'hush'. It's also notable as a vowelless word — one of only a few 2-letter words with no vowels." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is SH a vowelless Scrabble word?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, SH contains no vowels — it's purely consonants (S and H). In SOWPODS games, SH is one of the rare vowelless 2-letter words you can play. This makes it valuable when your rack is loaded with consonants and you can't find a vowel to use." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How many points is SH worth in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SH scores 5 points in Scrabble (S=1, H=4). The H tile is worth 4 points, making SH a relatively strong 2-letter play. On a Double Letter square for H, SH scores 9 points (8+1). On a Triple Letter for H, it scores 13 points (12+1)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is SH a Scrabble Word? SOWPODS Only (Not Valid in TWL)</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-23">June 23, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        SH is valid in SOWPODS (International) but NOT in TWL (North American). It scores 5 points and is an interjection meaning "be quiet" or "hush". What makes SH especially interesting is that it's a vowelless word — containing only consonants. In SOWPODS games, SH is a lifesaver when your rack is drowning in consonants.
      </p>

      <!-- Warning-Style Hero Card -->
