      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">SH is <span class="text-white font-medium">one of the strongest emergency plays</span> for consonant-heavy racks in SOWPODS. At 5 points with no vowels required, it lets you score while saving your vowels for better plays. The extension SHH (9pts) is valid in both dictionaries.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: When to Play SH</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Consonant overload:</span> Drew 5+ consonants? SH dumps two without needing a vowel. This frees rack space to draw vowels for your next turn.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">H on premium squares:</span> H is worth 4 points. On a Double Letter, H alone contributes 8 points — making SH score 9 total. On Triple Letter, SH scores 13 points for just 2 tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Preserve S for hooks:</span> Sometimes playing SH is less ideal because S is the most valuable hook letter. Consider whether saving S for a bigger hook play is worth more than the 5 immediate points.</p>
        </div>
